        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         We don\xe2\x80\x99t need to build a huge, permanent monolithic structure to have a big impact.
        </p>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         I want to bring in really smart, passionate people who are deeply knowledgeable about hard things and who can translate their knowledge into engaging essays, podcasts, papers, and more. If they want to pop in for a week and co-write a piece, great. If they want to build a career at Not Boring and spin up their own newsletter and fund under the umbrella one day, I would love that. A summer of research, meeting with companies, writing, and building up a reputation works just fine too. I\xe2\x80\x99d love it if people who work for Not Boring explore spinning up a company while they\xe2\x80\x99re here.
        </p>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         After resisting it, I think I know what this third year of Not Boring\xe2\x80\x99s life is going to be about\xe2\x80\xa6
        </p>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         <strong>
          Year 3: Growing a Team at Not Boring While
         </strong>
         <em>
          <strong>
           Enhancing
          </strong>
         </em>
         <strong>
          the Magic
         </strong>
        </p>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         I was hesitant to hire people because I pictured them trying to write the same things that I did, but just a little bit differently (and if I\xe2\x80\x99m being honest, in my head,
         <strong>
          worse
         </strong>
         ). It\xe2\x80\x99s funny that I wrote about Liquid Super Teams, but didn\xe2\x80\x99t fully appreciate that the concept applied to Not Boring:
        </p>
        <blockquote style="border-left: 4px solid #67bdfc; margin: 1em 0;">
         <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0; margin-left: 1em;">
          <em>
           Importantly, Liquid Super Teams allow each individual involved to bring their full powers to bear. They
           <strong>
            expose each person\xe2\x80\x99s full surface area
           </strong>
           , rather than hiding away parts inside of a larger sphere. If you compare one big sphere that has the same volume as ten smaller ones combined, the ten smaller spheres have roughly twice as much surface area as the big one.
          </em>
         </p>
        </blockquote>
        <div class="captioned-image-container-static" style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin-bottom: 16px; text-align: center;">
         <figure style="display: inline-block; margin: 0 auto; width: 100%;">
