        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         Someone on the Not Boring Liquid Super Team has a lot of paths to contribution, all of which involve following their curiosity. We just need to make sure that we have the right structure in place to maximize everyone\xe2\x80\x99s impact for the benefit of all of you and our portfolio companies.
        </p>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         So what\xe2\x80\x99s it going to look like? Glad you asked.
        </p>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         Each quarter, I share the (lightly redacted) LP Update to give you a peek behind the curtain and learn as I\xe2\x80\x99m learning. If you want to read this quarter\xe2\x80\x99s LP Update, you can check it out here:
        </p>
        <p class="button-wrapper" data-attrs='{"url":"https://www.notion.so/notboringcapital/Not-Boring-Capital-LP-Update-IV-Newsletter-Edition-c2599e92c9d3450bae42573458847e75","text":"Not Boring Capital LP Update IV","action":null,"class":"button-wrapper"}' style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0; text-align: center;">
         <a class="button primary button-wrapper" href="https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxFUU1rxCAQ_TXrLcHPRA8e2tJCoSy9tNdgdDYrm2gwpiH_vu4GWhAd3zDz5r2xJsMQ067nuGR0v7q8z6ADbMsIOUNC6wKp806ThkomuEJOc0ekkMgv3SUBTMaPOqcV0Lz2o7cm-xgeFRhTga6aCswswVz1LQbgRABthRKKOUlk49TBa1bnIVjQ8ANpjwHQqK85z8uJPZ3oWznbttUh3rvXSyz_Evcx-TBYM_tsxgKdY66eH1j1coDVx2f1Nbuis3r_rs5_uqpX5--tKkuFUqCoVY5xgXsDnIq2hFLyFlqBvKaYUswJIVRw3Na0vrRcSqYa4norDIaakzDvhJkTx9NA62Xtl2zsrbZxQkn_DVrSt6uZYHwkil1deac1-Lx3EEw_gjuczMdCHt52AwRIRYDrTC5r4KqRpGklI_xwrlgtiCK0aQQqzC6WqvBP-gvvCKCt" rel="" style="background-color: #67bdfc; border: none; border-radius: 4px; box-sizing: border-box; color: #ffffff !important; cursor: pointer; display: inline-block; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, 'Apple Color Emoji', 'Segoe UI Emoji', 'Segoe UI Symbol'; font-size: 16px; font-weight: normal; height: auto; line-height: 20px; margin: 0; opacity: 1; outline: none; padding: 12px 20px; text-align: center; text-decoration: none !important; white-space: nowrap;">
          <span style="color: #ffffff; text-decoration: none;">
           Not Boring Capital LP Update IV
          </span>
         </a>
        </p>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         Today, I want to go deeper on one of the sections from the update in particular:
         <strong>
          Growing Not Boring
         </strong>
         .
        </p>
        <h3 style="-moz-osx-font-smoothing: antialiased; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; color: #1a1a1a; font-family: 'SF Compact Display', -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, 'Apple Color Emoji', 'Segoe UI Emoji', 'Segoe UI Symbol'; font-size: 1.375em; font-weight: bold; line-height: 1.16em; margin: 1em 0 0.625em 0;">
         <strong>
          Building the Not Boring Liquid Super Team
         </strong>
        </h3>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         <em>
          <strong>
           From Not Boring Capital LP Update IV, Expanded Here
          </strong>
         </em>
        </p>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         For the two years I\xe2\x80\x99ve been writing Not Boring, and the one year I\xe2\x80\x99ve been running Not Boring Capital, one of the things that I appreciated most about it was the fact that it was
         <strong>
          just me
         </strong>
         .
        </p>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         No set meetings, no structure, no boss, and no reports (reports can often be more demanding than a boss). After 10 years in just two companies, most recently managing a team of 150 people, the lightness of being solo was freeing.
        </p>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         Over the past few months, though, I\xe2\x80\x99ve started to realize that, while I could keep doing everything
         <em>
          <strong>
           pretty well
          </strong>
         </em>
         on my own, I\xe2\x80\x99d need other people if I wanted to do it exceptionally well. Pretty well would have been fine. If you\xe2\x80\x99d told me two years ago that I could make a living off a newsletter and run a pretty good small fund, I\xe2\x80\x99d have taken that trade in a heartbeat.
        </p>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         But things change, and as Not Boring has grown, we\xe2\x80\x99ve built up assets that shouldn\xe2\x80\x99t go to waste:
        </p>
        <ul style="margin-top: 0;">
         <li style="margin-bottom: 4px; margin-left: 8px; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 4px; mso-special-format: bullet;">
          <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0; margin-bottom: 0;">
           A portfolio of
           <strong>
            ~200 companies
           </strong>
           , many of which are growing fast and tackling bigger opportunities than they originally set out to tackle.
          </p>
         </li>
         <li style="margin-bottom: 4px; margin-left: 8px; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 4px; mso-special-format: bullet;">
          <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0; margin-bottom: 0;">
           A newsletter with
           <strong>
            113k+ smart, curious readers
           </strong>
           and a
           <strong>
            Twitter following of 149k
           </strong>
           .
          </p>
         </li>
         <li style="margin-bottom: 4px; margin-left: 8px; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 4px; mso-special-format: bullet;">
          <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0; margin-bottom: 0;">
           A media property \xe2\x80\x93 the
           <strong>
            Sponsored Deep Dive
           </strong>
           \xe2\x80\x93 that is likely one of the most valuable on the internet and has been a better-than-expected way to meet great founders and help bend their companies\xe2\x80\x99 trajectories upwards.
          </p>
         </li>
         <li style="margin-bottom: 4px; margin-left: 8px; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 4px; mso-special-format: bullet;">
          <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0; margin-bottom: 0;">
           A diverse, non-institutional
           <strong>
            235-person-strong LP base
           </strong>
           , and demand from 1,500 more readers to back the Fund.
          </p>
         </li>
        </ul>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         Each time I think we\xe2\x80\x99ve plateaued, new things start happening that convince me that there\xe2\x80\x99s so much more room to run. Great founders introduce us to other great founders. A chance conversation about a piece turns into an investment opportunity. A podcast conversation kicks off a relationship with a genius founder. The
         <strong>
          Not Boring Flywheel
         </strong>
         spins faster and faster, in unexpected ways.
        </p>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         Ultimately, we\xe2\x80\x99ve quasi-accidentally built something rare \xe2\x80\x93 a
         <strong>
          differentiated VC fund
         </strong>
         \xe2\x80\x93 and I want to lean into that to build something special.
        </p>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         To get there, there\xe2\x80\x99s plenty of
         <strong>
          room for improvement
         </strong>
         . In the
         <a href="https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxFkN1uhCAQRp9G7tbwL15w0aTZ1zAIo0uqYHCs8e1L16RNGEjmy3AyxzuEOZfLbnlH8nsNeG1gE5z7AohQyLFDGWKwTHMjlOxJsDIwowyJ-zAVgNXFxWI5gGzHuETvMOb0nqCUK_KyynWTkLrvmXaynyho47VWwFU_ikmzm-uOECF5sPAN5coJyGJfiNveiI-GP-s5z7NNGcdcYppbn2trqxUTlhwOX5uPGj_u_OHdFtEtjXjWHz5PEi2nnFPJGONK0q7l7dRJY0SvWRi9chRaydJ2MeEaSdeZt_sx7uj8V2WtpNg_do2_Xm6F5R3UrYf6rkeKeA2Q3LhAuIXg7fWtaJghQam-w-Cw2pS9Nkx3RjB5C6jGFOsZr2pIJYdcp9I_9AdQSY-e" rel="" style="color: #1a1a1a; text-decoration: underline;">
          first memo
         </a>
         , I wrote that there were three things the fund needed to do to be successful:
        </p>
        <ul style="margin-top: 0;">
         <li style="margin-bottom: 4px; margin-left: 8px; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 4px; mso-special-format: bullet;">
          <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0; margin-bottom: 0;">
           <strong>
            Pick the Right Investments
           </strong>
          </p>
         </li>
         <li style="margin-bottom: 4px; margin-left: 8px; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 4px; mso-special-format: bullet;">
          <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0; margin-bottom: 0;">
           <strong>
            Win Allocations
           </strong>
          </p>
         </li>
         <li style="margin-bottom: 4px; margin-left: 8px; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 4px; mso-special-format: bullet;">
          <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0; margin-bottom: 0;">
           <strong>
            Help Portfolio Companies Succeed
           </strong>
          </p>
         </li>
        </ul>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         <strong>
          Pick the Right Investments
         </strong>
        </p>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         If picking the right investments is a
         <strong>
          combination of sourcing and picking
         </strong>
         , I\xe2\x80\x99d say our
         <strong>
          sourcing engine is a B+
         </strong>
         and our
         <strong>
          picking from that group is still too early to tell
         </strong>
         , but I really like our portfolio.
        </p>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         I give sourcing a B+ because while the newsletter and network we\xe2\x80\x99ve built has been very good for a one-person operation,
         <strong>
          there\xe2\x80\x99s more we could be doing to both proactively source early stage companies in particular
         </strong>
         , and learn when companies are raising a little bit earlier when allocation is more available. On the picking side, I could get a little more ambitious \xe2\x80\x93 push a little further out the
         <a href="https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxFkNGKhSAQhp8m7wo1tbrw4sByXiMmHTtySsNso7df9wS7oA78w8yHn4GMc0yX3uKeye8z5mtDHfDcF8wZEzl2TKO3minet1IMxGphWS974vfRJcQV_KJzOpBsx7R4A9nH8JmglEvy0hagc9JIaYyaOlROgGPKGONaOhkHNxcO6zEY1PiN6YoByaJfOW971T4q_iznPM8mxDzF5MPcmFiirdwS1XdWG9h8hqXmtTuCLeXOq_ZZtnydxGtOOaeCMcaloF3DG9eJvm8HxexkJFBsBAvbxVqoBF1n3uzHtGcw78JbSdJ__NJ-v2DF5dMoPx9LXY_g8zVigGlBe0vJt9uPpnHGgKk4tyPkYlQMqmeq61smbgnFmmQD40pJUsg2lqnwD_0BNFOSAQ" rel="" style="color: #1a1a1a; text-decoration: underline;">
          weirdness curve
         </a>
         \xe2\x80\x93 if there were people on the team with deeper technical knowledge.
        </p>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         <strong>
          Win Allocations
         </strong>
        </p>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         We have been
         <strong>
          successful in winning allocations
         </strong>
         . I can only think of one or two deals that we wanted to get into and didn\xe2\x80\x99t, and we\xe2\x80\x99ve recently been able to write larger and larger checks in competitive rounds.
        </p>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         It\xe2\x80\x99s still TBD whether and how often we\xe2\x80\x99re able to scale to even larger checks, which I believe will be a function of the resources we can bring to bear for companies.
        </p>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         <strong>
          Help Portfolio Companies Succeed
         </strong>
        </p>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         Lastly, I think we\xe2\x80\x99ve done a
         <strong>
          pretty good job at helping certain companies succeed
         </strong>
         \xe2\x80\x93 when I write a Deep Dive, that no doubt helps, and I try to be helpful behind the scenes too \xe2\x80\x93 but I can\xe2\x80\x99t write Deep Dives on every company. That said, there are some low-hanging ways to leverage Not boring\xe2\x80\x99s unique assets to help companies even more.
        </p>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         Ultimately, after self-analysis, I realized that we have too incredible an opportunity to give away, and that all of the shortcomings we have can be fixed by bringing on
         <strong>
          talented people
         </strong>
         .
        </p>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         So
         <strong>
          we\xe2\x80\x99re hiring
         </strong>
         .
        </p>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         The lowest-hanging fruit, and something I should have done a long time ago, is to bring on an Executive Assistant (EA). I\xe2\x80\x99ve avoided this for too long because I\xe2\x80\x99ve been worried that it would take more time to onboard them than I\xe2\x80\x99d save, or because I thought I\xe2\x80\x99d look like an asshole \xe2\x80\x9clooping in my EA,\xe2\x80\x9d but enough people have told me that I\xe2\x80\x99m an idiot for not doing it that I pulled the trigger. I have an onboarding call this afternoon with an EA from
         <a href="https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxFkMuOhCAQRb-mWRpAUFiwmM38BuFRrWQUDJTT8e-HbheTEEiqcjk5NziEpdTLHKUheV8WrwNMhlfbABEqORtUm6JhE1ejFJpEIyJTUpHU7LMC7C5tBusJ5Dj9loLDVPInQSmXZO1JFsI8S6WF9N7BqMMsuJNj1FE-Pb257owJcgADv1CvkoFsZkU82mP8evDvfl4J11g6A4ZQ9j4gyXDKORWMMS4FnQc-PGeh1KgnFn2QjsIgWD4uNrqHoPvCh3b6hi78vL8g1eSCvtSUl77-Wd0O22fRTWx_9zMnvCxk16HxlsS7q4-2XSBD7R1G67B7Cj0pNs1qZOKW6i1IphmfJkk6OZaeyv_QP2ewgEw" rel="" style="color: #1a1a1a; text-decoration: underline;">
          Double
         </a>
         . Hopefully I get some more leverage and can do more myself with an EA, and at the very least, my inbox and calendar won\xe2\x80\x99t be such minefields. I also\xc2\xa0won\xe2\x80\x99t miss as many emails, which, ironically, will make me look like less of an asshole.
        </p>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         More importantly, I\xe2\x80\x99m building out a lightweight but talent-dense team to make us great where we\xe2\x80\x99re only OK currently.
        </p>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         First things first:
         <strong>
          helping portfolio companies succeed
         </strong>
         . That has direct benefits in the form of more valuable companies, and indirect benefits in the ability to get more follow-on allocation and in founders introducing us to other great founders.
        </p>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         To that end, at the start of the month, my brother
         <strong>
          <a href="https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxFkE1uxCAMhU8zLCP-QxYsuuk1IgNOBk0CEZBWuX2ZyaKSZcuy7Of3eWi45nLZI9dG3mlu14E24W_dsDUs5KxY5hgs09wIJScSrAzMKENinZeCuEPcbCsnkuN0W_TQYk6fDUq5Ik_rXRiXaVEMKQivtEQvHHAG3mgnIdy6cIaIyaPFHyxXTkg2-2ztqA_x9eDfPdpvfH80-Lz3LsDufS579C8mSLScck4lY4wrSceBD8sojRGTZsF5BRQHydJxMQEPSfeVD_V0tYF_ve-RYlNuLpeY1j5-PWHH7TPonuZe9zPFds2YwG0YbrvtpvYBMK-YsHSaYYbWWclJG6ZHI5i87XUeik2Ma61IVw65b6V_0T_JrYTl" rel="" style="color: #1a1a1a; text-decoration: underline;">
           Dan
          </a>
          joined me as Chief of Staff
         </strong>
         for the media business and the fund. He\xe2\x80\x99s been helping out for free \xe2\x80\x93 editing essays, strategizing on growth, and more \xe2\x80\x93 while running Finance &amp; Operations at Parade, which recently raised $20M at a $140M valuation in a
         <a href="https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxFkcGupCAQRb-m2WEAQXHB4m3eb5hCSps0ggEc43z90N2LSQgFVIp7cu8CFbeUb3OkUsl7m-t9oIl4lYC1YiZnwTx7Z_ggdK_kRJyRjmuliS_zmhF38MHUfCI5Thv8AtWn-JlgTCjyNGCncR2UklatOCi9Ws3H3gknR74At19dOJ3HuKDBP5jvFJEE86z1KI_-5yF-27quq7Mhpd1i3rol7e3tDdoK5OqXgO-jYIJTNtGetcuGkf6lZ3SYL4RMbYbo6AEZHNIMvmChgtHdh9CgaU10y-miaV2DbwTetN8Ek5xzoSQbO9Gto9S6nwbu7KKAYSd5PG7ew0OyfRNdOW2psLzefCSbmKpN2cettV9P2DF8Gs2pudX9jL7eM0awAd3XxPrN4mPr3Pgxt4zcDLUlIKdB82HUPZdf05rLik9cDIMiTdmlNhX_i_4D5rOhgg" rel="" style="color: #1a1a1a; text-decoration: underline;">
          Stripes-led Series B
         </a>
         .
        </p>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         Dan has been an unofficial fixture, which I highlighted a year ago when I wrote
         <em>
          <a href="https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxFkN1qxCAQRp9mvUvwP8mFF4WyrxFGnc1KEw3GbMjb125KC-rAN8wcPA4KTimfZk1bIT_PWM4VTcRjm7EUzGTfMI_BG6Z5L5QciDfSs171JGzjIyMuEGZT8o5k3e0cHJSQ4nuCUq7I0whmrbNag3dWKs2RO4qdouKhYBikvLiw-4DRocEX5jNFJLN5lrJuN_Fx4_d6juNoYyo25RCn1qUarfVCU8PmShvwL4xlz9jUDc2JkJsQb-Jet3weJBhOOaeSMcaVpF3L20cn-14MmnnrFFBsJYvryQTcJF0m3m673Qq4r8pbSDZ__Nr-esKC87tRfz7WuuwxlHPECHZGf0kpl9u3pnHCiLk69yOUalQOume66wX7lVCtKTYwrrUilexTnYr_0G8MxpE3" rel="" style="color: #1a1a1a; text-decoration: underline;">
           A Not Boring Adventure, One Year In
          </a>
         </em>
         :
        </p>
