        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         To start, Dan will be
         <strong>
          leading the business side of Not Boring Media
         </strong>
         , freeing up more of my time for writing and investing, along with setting both the media business and the fund up to scale. (If you want to sponsor or partner with Not Boring,
         <a href="https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxFkE1uxCAMhU8zLCP-QxYsuuk1IgNOBk0CEZBWuX2ZyaKSZcuy7Of3eWi45nLZI9dG3mlu14E24W_dsDUs5KxY5hgs09wIJScSrAzMKENinZeCuEPcbCsnkuN0W_TQYk6fDUq5Ik_rXRiXaVEMKQivtEQvHHAG3mgnIdy6cIaIyaPFHyxXTkg2-2ztqA_x9eDfPdpvfH80-Lz3LsDufS579C8mSLScck4lY4wrSceBD8sojRGTZsF5BRQHydJxMQEPSfeVD_V0tYF_ve-RYlNuLpeY1j5-PWHH7TPonuZe9zPFds2YwG0YbrvtpvYBMK-YsHSaYYbWWclJG6ZHI5i87XUeik2Ma61IVw65b6V_0T_JrYTl" rel="" style="color: #1a1a1a; text-decoration: underline;">
          hit him up
         </a>
         !)
        </p>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         One of the advantages that Not Boring has is that we can build new business lines on the media side that we can also leverage to help our portfolio companies. That should mean that
         <strong>
          we can afford to do even more things to help companies than a similarly-sized fund could on management fees alone
         </strong>
         .
        </p>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         So
         <strong>
          Dan\xe2\x80\x99s primary mandate is to figure out more ways to scalably help our portfolio companies
         </strong>
         \xe2\x80\x93 to work with the smart, curious audience we\xe2\x80\x99ve built to help founders in the highest-leverage way possible. Even as we scale our check sizes, we want Not Boring to be the most bang for the buck on the cap table, and we want to be able to continue to write smaller checks into earlier stage companies without breaking the model. I couldn\xe2\x80\x99t do that alone, and Dan\xe2\x80\x99s already making strides. His first two initiatives were launching a revamped
         <strong>
          Not Boring Founders podcast
         </strong>
         and setting up the
         <strong>
          Not Boring Talent Collective with Pallet
         </strong>
         .
        </p>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         <strong>
          Not Boring Founders Podcast
         </strong>
        </p>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         Over the past year or so, I\xe2\x80\x99ve been casually interviewing founders on and off on our podcast feed, but it\xe2\x80\x99s been sporadic and unstructured. I\xe2\x80\x99m no Ben Gilbert, David Rosenthal, Harry Stebbings, or Patrick O\xe2\x80\x99Shaughnessy.
        </p>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         Dan has already begun to revamp
         <strong>
          <a href="https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxFkE9LxDAQxT9NcyyZ_GnTQw6KLIiK4M1TSZPpbtg2KUmq9tsbdw_CMAPzeLyZnzUFzzEdeou5kL82lmNDHfA7L1gKJrJnTKN3GjqmuBQDcVo4UFIRn8c5Ia7GL7qkHcm2T4u3pvgYbg5KmSQXzSRlDBTS2Q6OdXSwXFLo515RnAZu77lmdx6DRY1fmI4YkCz6UsqWG_7QsFOtuGFo8xaLn4_WxrWu8iV-19Fd4fP18ev94-PtiPnl4D_w87w0_JR9w58ETrOSg0QwKGj9wGtWL6ICAJgUtG9ZO_dCKT504CYrDcVWQNgO4KYRdD2zNu9TLsZe_3JJ0iGWKSYfzlW-XsyKy02oAMY61z34cowYzLSgu7Mpd8Q3WuMZA6aK3o2mVLBi6BR0veIg7iwqPAkDsK6TpCa7WF3hP_QXfGGQ3Q" rel="" style="color: #1a1a1a; text-decoration: underline;">
           Not Boring Founders
          </a>
         </strong>
         (subscribe to meet some of your portfolio founders). He landed
         <a href="https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxFkE2OhCAQRk_TLA0gIC5YzKavQfgpbSKCAZyJc_qh28UEQiVUqr6850yDNZdLHbk29H50uw5QCX5qhNagoLNC0cErIqgcOZuRV8wTySUKVS8FYDchqlZOQMdpY3CmhZw-ExhTjl6KcBhnzqUhxgjBMGViIjMRk4RJEjvdueb0AZIDBd9QrpwARfVq7aiP8etBn_3GkLbBxuy2JceQB5f3_jv736MXgMXTflBQFFOKGSGEcoangQ7LxKQcZ0G8ddxgGBhJx0VG82B4X-lQT1ubcdt7Iyoq5WZzCWnt7e1ldoifRqfTve5nCu3SkIyN4G_wdvv7qNArJCjdq9emdWtsFvLNOhJ2g3YzvONTITjqyT73qfQf-geQXoXf" rel="" style="color: #1a1a1a; text-decoration: underline;">
          FTX US
