         , and pushed me to make it more structured. Now, we start every conversation with three questions:
        </p>
        <ol style="margin-top: 0;">
         <li style="margin-bottom: 4px; margin-left: 8px; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 4px;">
          <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0; margin-bottom: 0;">
           What does the world look like in a decade if you\xe2\x80\x99re wildly successful?
          </p>
         </li>
         <li style="margin-bottom: 4px; margin-left: 8px; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 4px;">
          <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0; margin-bottom: 0;">
           What does [company] do today?
          </p>
         </li>
         <li style="margin-bottom: 4px; margin-left: 8px; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 4px;">
          <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0; margin-bottom: 0;">
           What will it take to get from here to there?
          </p>
         </li>
        </ol>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         Since re-launching, we\xe2\x80\x99ve had seven conversations with founders (six from the portfolio and one outside of it).
