         </strong>
        </p>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         <strong>
          Website
         </strong>
        </p>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         We\xe2\x80\x99ve survived two years without our own website. It\xe2\x80\x99s probably time to grow up. There\xe2\x80\x99s nothing revolutionary about a website obviously \xe2\x80\x93 we\xe2\x80\x99re in the small minority of funds who don\xe2\x80\x99t have one \xe2\x80\x93 but I think we can do some valuable things with ours given Not Boring\xe2\x80\x99s audience. We\xe2\x80\x99re planning to get this live in the next couple of months, working with a couple portfolio companies of course.
        </p>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         Having Dan onboard and letting him loose on the tools at our disposal is a multiplier \xe2\x80\x93 we should be able to add more value to portfolio companies without needing to build out a platform team.
        </p>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         Having him onboard also means that we can
         <strong>
          bring on more people without slowing down
         </strong>
         .
        </p>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         <strong>
          Hiring Research Analysts
         </strong>
        </p>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         To that end, we\xe2\x80\x99re opening up two roles I\xe2\x80\x99ve been dreaming about for a while:
        </p>
        <ul style="margin-top: 0;">
         <li style="margin-bottom: 4px; margin-left: 8px; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 4px; mso-special-format: bullet;">
          <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0; margin-bottom: 0;">
           <strong>
            Atoms Research Analyst
           </strong>
          </p>
         </li>
         <li style="margin-bottom: 4px; margin-left: 8px; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 4px; mso-special-format: bullet;">
          <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0; margin-bottom: 0;">
           <strong>
            Bits Research Analyst
           </strong>
          </p>
         </li>
        </ul>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         When Not Boring is at its best, we\xe2\x80\x99re
         <strong>
          explaining and investing in new things that push the limits of what\xe2\x80\x99s possible.
         </strong>
        </p>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         Writing about a SaaS company can be interesting, but there are a lot of people who do it better than I can. Explaining
         <a href="https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxFkNuKgzAQhp-muatkcqq5yMXC0teQmIwaqonEuOLbb1phF-YAc_qZz9mCY8qnWdNWyDt05VzRRDy2GUvBTPYNcxe8AcVaLoUm3ggPrWxJ2LohIy42zKbkHcm693NwtoQUPxuUMkkmI711XA0KmWege6UGTrXmliGAk0xfunb3AaNDgz-YzxSRzGYqZd1u_OvGntWO42hiKn3KIY6NS7W0Vi8T3r1N9zS8Ux1_Vv8-SDCMMkYFADAp6KNhzfAQbcu1At87aSk2AuJ6Arc3QZeRNdveb8W6Vz2-kGz-xGr7NdkF50-jvtnVvOwxlLPDaPsZ_UWgXCA_TLoRI-YK2He2VHxCqxbUo-Ugro8rIgkamFKSVGWf6lb8F_0FNSyJgA" rel="" style="color: #1a1a1a; text-decoration: underline;">
          DAOs
         </a>
         or
         <a href="https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxFkMFuhSAQRb_msathEEQXLLrpb5gR5vnIUzCANf59qSZtMswkTObe3GOx0BzTabaYC_ttYzk3MoGOvFAplNieKY3eGehE3yo5MGekg171zOfxmYhW9IspaSe27dPiLRYfw3XBuVDsZUCjQJTYqkFr2yLXVuuqocFJDdjdvrg7T8GSoW9KZwzEFvMqZcuP9vMhvmodx9GEWKaYfJgbG-vXVl8uWPb8scbwpjMzbwQXgksAEEpy3YjmqWXft0MHbrIKOTUSwnZCiw_J11k0eZ-qiH1XzZUl8-dR1-8XrrRci5purHPdgy_nSAGnhdwdvNz8LhTjTIFS5epGLJWaHLoeOt23IO-glYyCAUTXKVadXaxX4d_0BxD_h4E" rel="" style="color: #1a1a1a; text-decoration: underline;">
          NFTs
         </a>
         before most people knew what they were, or writing about
         <a href="https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxFkNGKhSAQhp8m7wo17diFFwvLeY0YdSo5pWG2bW-_7gl2wXFghp-P-SxknGK69Bb3TH6_IV8b6oDnvmDOmMixYxq806zjqpWiJ04Lx5RUxO_DmBBX8IvO6UCyHWbxFrKP4Z2glEsy655LMGDbfpQUe1CADKS0ho9CGNfJmwuH8xgsavzCdMWAZNFzzttetR8Vf5Z3nmcTYjYx-TA1NpbRVmoGlzyEGr_rFezsA9Tg6uUIsFbts8Q_T-I1p5xTwRjjUtBHw5vxIZRq-445YyVQbAQL28VaqARdJ97sh9kz2FcBrSTpP3BZv2ZYcXkvyslD6esRfL4GDGAWdLeNfEt9-xkmDJiKbDdALipF3ynWPVTLxH190SVZz3hXdBSyiyUV_qE_MsqO3g" rel="" style="color: #1a1a1a; text-decoration: underline;">
          Hadrian
         </a>
         and what it means for America and space, is where I think we can have the biggest impact. The
         <a href="https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxFkN1qxCAQhZ8m3jU4aoy58GKh7GsEo7NZ2UTFmIb06Ws30ML8wAxnDvNZU3CO-dQpboX8lrGcCXXAY1uwFMxk3zCP3mmQTPFODMRp4UB1ivhtfGTE1fhFl7wjSfu0eGuKj-GtoJR15Kk54wNY6QY3KWG44eCs7AUIyywIOly-Znceg0WNX5jPGJAs-llK2hp-a9i9xnEcbYhlitmHubWxjlJNG9cU9-Dq8MNm8302_F5FnwfxmlHGqAAA1gnat6x99EIpPkhwk-0MxVZASCdw0wi6zqzd9mkrxr7q-ZVk_WdX16-nWXF5L-qjY-3rHnw5RwxmWtBdDMqF8k1lnDFgrojdaEoFKAapQPaKg7h-rpA6GIBJ2ZHq7GJVhX_TH7FpisU" rel="" style="color: #1a1a1a; text-decoration: underline;">
          world continues to get crazier
         </a>
         , and I want people to
         <strong>
          meet all of the change with curiosity and optimism instead of cynicism and fear.
         </strong>
        </p>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         But I\xe2\x80\x99m more curious than smart, and I\xe2\x80\x99m probably a little
         <em>
          too
         </em>
         optimistic.
        </p>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         So I want to hire two people to the team who are:
        </p>
        <ul style="margin-top: 0;">
         <li style="margin-bottom: 4px; margin-left: 8px; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 4px; mso-special-format: bullet;">
          <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0; margin-bottom: 0;">
           <strong>
            Up-and-coming experts
           </strong>
           in their fields,
          </p>
         </li>
         <li style="margin-bottom: 4px; margin-left: 8px; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 4px; mso-special-format: bullet;">
          <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0; margin-bottom: 0;">
           Much more
           <strong>
            technical
           </strong>
           than I am, and
          </p>
         </li>
         <li style="margin-bottom: 4px; margin-left: 8px; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 4px; mso-special-format: bullet;">
          <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0; margin-bottom: 0;">
           Know how to
           <strong>
            write well
           </strong>
           .
          </p>
         </li>
        </ul>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         I realize that we\xe2\x80\x99re looking for needles in a haystack, people who have a lot of amazing options, and in return, I\xe2\x80\x99m hoping that I can offer them space to
         <strong>
          explore broadly
         </strong>
         , a
         <strong>
          platform
         </strong>
         , and a chance to
         <strong>
          hone their storytelling skills
         </strong>
         . Technical people who can tell a compelling story are hard to beat.
        </p>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         The
         <strong>
          Atoms Research Analyst
         </strong>
         will be someone who loves reading (and writing) research papers and doing science in the physical world. They might specialize in Climate, Space, Biotech, or some other corner of Deep Tech, but above all else, I want them to have a passion for, and familiarity with, everything going on at the frontier, and an ability to explain those things to normal people, like me. They\xe2\x80\x99ll help source and analyze deep tech investments, write company memos, and write research reports that go out to all of you.
        </p>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         The
         <strong>
          Bits Research Analyst
         </strong>
         will be someone who thinks at the speed of the internet and understands all of the latest, wildest things happening in web3. They can see a pile of Legos and make an educated guess as to how they might snap together. They\xe2\x80\x99re ideally technical, or technical enough to be dangerous, familiar with the most interesting people and projects in web3, and able to explain complex concepts simply and engagingly. They\xe2\x80\x99ll help source and analyze web3 investments, live in Discords and Telegrams, write project memos, and put together research reports that go out to all of you.
        </p>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         In both cases, I want people who share my optimism, but who are willing to tell me when I\xe2\x80\x99m being more optimistic than the science or vibes suggest I should be.
        </p>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         We\xe2\x80\x99re
         <strong>
          open to interns, fellows, x-in-residences, part-time analysts, or full-time analysts, local in NYC or remote, pseudonymous or doxxed
         </strong>
         . Those titles are written in pencil; we can specialize and expand. If building a
         <a href="https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxFkE2OhCAQRk_T7NoAAuKCxWzmGgahWkkrECzHePuhNZlJ-EmofPWo5yzClMppctqQfI4BzwwmwrEtgAiF7BuUIXjDFNetFD3xRnimpSZhG14FYLVhMVh2IHkfl-AshhSvBKVcktnYVo6qRl4SJOuc6KxVWgghme0o9-PNtbsPEB0Y-IFypghkMTNi3h7t14N_13UcRxMTjqmEODUu1adcN87wdCllKBf5CS7FtJ5PEgynnFPBGONS0K7hzasTWre9Yn500lJoBIv5ZK19CLpOvNn2cUPr3rX7Sor5o9Xye7YrLFehzjnUe91jwHOAaMcF_K0Ab5OXlGGC-PkU-MFi9Sd6pZnqdMvEPXJ1JFnPuFKSVLJPNRX_ob_aKotC" rel="" style="color: #1a1a1a; text-decoration: underline;">
          Liquid Super Team
         </a>
         means being able to bring people we otherwise couldn\xe2\x80\x99t onboard, I\xe2\x80\x99m all for it. I just want the best and brightest. We\xe2\x80\x99ll expand to more positions over time as people specialize.
        </p>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         Hell, if there\xe2\x80\x99s a different role that you think we should be hiring for instead of these roles and aren\xe2\x80\x99t, hijack the application and let us know.
        </p>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         I just want Not Boring to be known as a place where really smart people can come to both learn and teach, for as little as one newsletter or as long as a career. I want it to be cross-disciplinary \xe2\x80\x93 I think that some of the greatest opportunities will come at the intersection of Bits and Atoms, and I hope that we can both discover and generate the coolest things happening at those intersections. Above all else, I want it to be fun, an opportunity for high-horsepower people to relax, explore, dream, and translate what they find to our audience.
        </p>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         You can find
         <a href="https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxFUV2L3SAQ_TXXtwQ1GvXBh7Z0YaEsfWlfgx-Te2UTDWbSkn9f9wa2IOPgmcPxnAkO4V7qabeyI_koE54b2Ax_9wUQoZJjhzqlaNnI9SCFIdGKyLTUJO3TXAFWlxaL9QCyHX5JwWEq-cmglEvysJJr4digFIMR5tH4mUmtqB_iDLP0cOm6IybIASz8gXqWDGSxD8Rtvw1fbvylnVzQl5ryPbgtoVv69tCk-j0hNPitYPf1iXffroHux8_u1xabx-71d_f26an7HtMHswtcGgOGBxMHIal3ILhUrdVaKFCSJMsp51QwxrgUVPW8n5XQejAjiz5IR6EXLG8nG9xN0PXO-_3wO7rw3oeykmo_P93g94dbYXkCLaqp3euRE54TZOcXiFeKeC3jmet0hwy1GYiTw7YCYUbNRqUHJq7UWsySGcbHUZKmHEtj5f-i_wAqw6Cg" rel="" style="color: #1a1a1a; text-decoration: underline;">
          job descriptions and applications here
         </a>
         . Be warned:
         <strong>
          applicants are going to have to write
         </strong>
         : 1,000 words on the most fascinating company or trend in their space.
        </p>
        <p class="button-wrapper" data-attrs='{"url":"https://www.notion.so/notboringcapital/Not-Boring-Atoms-Bits-Research-Analysts-96013910354347a3a3b839782af5d018","text":"Apply to Join Not Boring","action":null,"class":"button-wrapper"}' style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0; text-align: center;">
